text15.content: 1. Period life expectancy: Period life expectancy is a metric that summarizes death rates across all age groups in one particular year. For a givenyear, it represents the average lifespan for a hypothetical group of people, if they experienced the same age-specific death rates throughout theirwhole lives as the age-specific death rates seen in that particular year. Learn more in our article: “Life expectancy” – What does this actually mean?
